Two former Eskom executives will be back in
court on charges of fraud, corruption and money laundering in connection with the
Eskom Kusile R745m corruption and fraud case on Tuesday. Former Eskom group executive for the Group Capital
Division, Abram Masango, former contracts manager, France Hlakudi, will be appearing alongside businessman
Maphoko Kgomoeswana, and Tubular Construction chief executive officer, Antonio Trindade, at the Palm Ridge Specialised Commercial Crimes Court in Johannesburg. Michael Lomas, a former Tubular holdings advisor, will not be
in court as he is still in the United Kingdom. He is, however, expected
to make an court appearance on December 20 and 21 in the London Westminster
Magistrates' Court where his extradition trial will begin.  